    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.30 Asiatic Fleet/563½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-30">August 30,
                            1938</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Navy Department has just informed
                    me that Admiral Leahy has an appointment with the President at 11:15 this
                    morning. If you are still at the White House at that time you and Admiral Leahy
                    may care to speak to the President in regard to the question of the U. S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> proceeding to Shanghai.</p>
                <p>A memorandum in regard to the <hi rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> case is
                        attached.<note n="35" xml:id="d213fn35">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">axwell</hi>] M. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >amilton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
